<br>
As I said in my original post, I was in a deep depression and I had several social problems, I felt alone, even felt like I had no reason to live, and I met someone that would shift the direction of my life from that point.<br>
<br>
She was gorgeous, and I felt grotesque, and I don't mean it only in a phisical way. She was charismatic, amaible and really beatiful, but at that time I was so close-minded that I felt she was completely out of my league, as a friend, as a person, as a woman.<br>
<br>
Then I remembered I met her a year ago, we used to have a class together in the last year of high school, we really didn't talk much, but I really had good thoughts about her.<br>
<br>
For my surprise she was really interested in me, as a person.<br>
I really thought that I would finally overcome this depression in where I was living, she actually had a boyfriend, but I ignored that fact, and decided it was safe to get to know her as deep as I could. <br>
<br>
We develop a wonderful friendship, something that although sounds good, it was not, because when I was starting to develop feelings for her, she felt honest to tell me everything about her, including how wonderful her boyfriend was with her, and I started to realized that I got myself into the worst nightmare. <br>
<br>
But I kept dreaming that everything could work out as I wanted, ( and I still do ), we were best friends, we would talk for hours, but each time she would talk about her boyfriend I would felt so bad I wanted to literally die, from time to time I felt worse about it, I couln't live without her, and she started noticing that I was acting a little bit weird, so in a sane way she confronted me, and I told her what I felt.<br>
<br>
She has been like an angel to me, she helps me out whenever I need help, and viceversa, so she understood my situation, but she couldn't deny how much she loved her boyfriend, so she told me that it was best to split up, since she didn't wanted to be responsible to hurt my feelings, I felt liberated, for a bit, but as the days passed, I couldn't concentrate in anything, I thought about her all the time, and I wrote her an e-mail, about what I was feeling. <br>
<br>
I told her how I missed her, as a friend, and I said that I will do my best to ignore those feelings because our friendship was so important. I failed to do that. Two months later I am loving her more and more, I think she forgot all about that week, and in the present we still talk as much, we are still best friends, and I still dream that somehow things will work out in the future, she really loves me as a friend, and I want to believe that she can feel someday that I can be more than that.<br>
<br>
But I really wonder if I am doing things right, my love is not selfish, I want the best for her, and I want it for me too, and I know I would be the happiest man in the world if I was with her, of course, I wouldn't feel happy if she was with me without real love.<br>
<br>
I really wonder what should I do, I have thought many times about trying to forget her, I have tried to meet other people, tried to ignore her a little bit and stop getting together, but I just can't, I love her too much as a person, as a friend, as a woman. <br>
<br>
What should I do? split up? something that would prolly break my heart, or be patient and wait?, If you can, please let me know what you think, I know she loves me very much as a friend, as much as I do, just that my loves goes beyond that point.<br>
<br>
Thanks and my apologies for the length of the post, like I said in the last one, it really takes long for me to express my feelings. <br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
