<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie" target="top">Firiona Vie</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kanoganv>KanoganV</A> at: 4/28/03 11:11:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tammitha>Tammitha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/28/03 11:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/2339864.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Was wondering. #2</span><hr size=1> Well, I'm no Freud or even Abby, but I can try to give what I can.<br>
<br>
We can't help feeling how we do, despite our best interests. But we can try to nudge ourselves away from things that will cause us pain. I think the worst thing you could do is just quit this girl cold turkey. For all practical purposes, you sound lie the best of friends, and nothing's worth losing that over. However, that said, you need to confront yourself with the reality of how things are, and most likely, how they will be. If you truely love someone, deep down, then you will want what's best for them, what makes them happy, no matter what. Sure, I know it's hard letting her go in &quot;that way&quot;, but that doesn't mean you have to lose the friendship.<br>
<br>
I know moving on doesn't seem to be working, but I think perhaps you need an epiphany before it can. And I think you need to, before you dig yourself too deep into something that is at heart just a fantasy. If you don't know him well, meet her boyfriend. If you already have, and he's a great guy, then try to make him a friend as well. After all, if they are both your friends, the only thing you'd be losing is the intimate parts...and while I'm sure it's tempting to think about those, true love is a lot more than that. If he's not a great guy, let her know, but don't try to break her heart. After all, I'm sure you don't want her to end up with someone that you know will hurt her in the end, but hurting her now to prevent hurt later isn't exactly the way to do things.<br>
<br>
You need to get to a point where you can smile becaause she smiles, frown when she frowns, laugh when she laughs...and not care about the what's and why's. If she's happy about being with her boyfriend, you should be happy that she's found such ahppiness. If she gets married to him someday, you should try to be the one crying tears of sappy joy at the ceremony, because you know she's so happy as well. Can you find happiness on your own, aside from her? Sure you can. Will it take time? Yes, and certainly work as well. You have to remember that it's not only what's best for her, but also best for you, and dwellnig on her like this isn't the best thing you can do for yourself. Cherishing the friendship you have, seeking someone she can be happy you are with...these are goals you should work for, mno matter how difficult they might seem to be.<br>
<br>
Hm, I hope that ramble helped. Just remember: you love her, and that means accepting that she might love someone else as well, and that it's not a stronger love nessisarily, just a diferent kind. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/2342310.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kanoganv>KanoganV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 338<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/03 12:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/paladin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Was wondering. #2</span><hr size=1> .I read everything you said, I admit the true might hurt sometimes, and some thoughts I had really did, and I will try to ignore my feelings, maybe I am being a little selfish.<br>
<br>
But besides that, you think there is any posibility of us happening, she is just 19, I am not sure if he will be the man of her life, and I may be exagerating, but I want to be that man, I fear that feeling, I don't want to get obsessive, but it keeps coming back to me.<br>
<br>
I just hope at the end we both can be happy, in the way life decided it to happen, if we end together, great, if we end with someone else, also great as long as we are both happy. But I just don't want to suffer what I am suffering anymore, I am so confused. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=635758" target="top"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:navy;font-size:medium;">Kanogan Val'Kad</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
