<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie" target="top">Firiona Vie</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tammitha>Tammitha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/03 12:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/2339864.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Was wondering. #2</span><hr size=1> Well, there's always a possibility. The future can take a lot of sharp turns, and usually in ways we never even thought of possible. You're both young, and you have plenty of time to work out what you think, what you feel. I don't want you to ignore your feelings. On the contrary, that's the worst thnig yuo can do. Do you love her? Good, then don't <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ever</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> tell yourself you don't. What you should do is try to work out those feelings, try to reanalyze them. <br>
<br>
That thought about being together in matrimony? Try to think of it as being happy friends, and you visiting their house once a week or something. Should you stop thinking of the possibility that things might go differently, that you might end up together? Well, not in the strictest sense: everyone should dream. But you can't focus your life solely on one dream, and think that that's the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> way things should turn out.<br>
<br>
She talked to you before about stuff like this: maybe you should talk to her again. Try to ask how happy she would be with a friend like you, even if things could never go beyond that. You'll have to ask yourself that as well. Obviously, if things go different, you can ask her how shou'd feel about being more tha nfriends. But in the meantime, you just have to accept what you've got, and that's a precious and dear friends that you could lose if you try to worry about it like you are.<br>
<br>
Life is rather confusing, and at times it can hurt no matter what we do. But you decide to aim yourself towards a path that will leve you both happy, even if it's not perfect, if you try.<br>
<br>
*hugs and warm smiles* <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/2342310.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tammitha>Tammitha</A> at: 4/29/03 12:52:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fallnangel77>Fallnangel77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/03 5:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pic4.picturetrail.com/VOL55/1072917/2013975/24137154.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Was wondering. #2</span><hr size=1> You should not ignore your feelings. That is probably the worst thing you can do. You need to accept how you feel while at the same time accepting the situation. Try to accept that now you two are good friends and that is all that you are, for now. You never know what the future holds but it seems that all she wants from you is friendship at this time. This is something she appears to treasure, so accept that she may only want this and try to be open to having feelings for others. <br>
<br>
From what I have gathered by your two posts I think I see something of an underlying problem. You are depressed, lonely, and lack self confidence. Now you have this person in your life that brings you happiness, companionship, and someone that you can talk to. The possible problem I see is that you are somewhat using this person to fill in this lack of self confidence and depression, like a crutch. Much like with your escape into the world of EQ, you are missing the problem by concentrating on her. I strongly advise you to back off from her, not physically distance yourself or the friendship, but your feelings for her. This does not mean ignore them. You need to move your attention from her to yourself and deal with yourself. It is dangerous to draw your happiness and confidence from another person instead of yourself. Once you have dealt with your problems and have found your inner peace, happiness, and self confidence then you be much more stable and ready for any such relationship. Happiness does not come from without, but from within. Yes others can make us happy, but you will never be truly happy until you are happy with yourself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kanoganv>KanoganV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/29/03 12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/animations/paladin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Was wondering. #2</span><hr size=1> I guess you guys are right, I must face what I fell with everything I have, I cannot ignore my feelings and much less ignore her, but I guess I need to dedicate time to myself, sadly I have been too focused in finding a solution and been lacking in various obligations I have with myself, my friends and my family. I will dedicate time to think about me, and then, I'll worry about her.<br>
<br>
